[savestate_save / savestate_load]
Rationale: Flat binary format, no compression. ~3.5MB reads in <1ms from SSD.
Sections: RAM (2MB), Scratchpad (1KB), Runtime globals, GPU state, VRAM (1MB), SPU (512KB+voices), XA LBA.
Save point is after Present() in psx_present_frame() — clean frame boundary.

[psx_recreate_fibers]
Rationale: Windows Fibers can't be serialized (native C stack). On load, delete existing fibers
and recreate from saved entry points. Compiled functions are infinite loops that read all state
from g_ram/g_scratch each iteration — re-entering at function entry with correct RAM state works.

[script_load / script_poll]
Rationale: Simple text format for automated input sequences. "press X" = hold 1 frame + release.
Frame counter advances on each poll (once per psx_present_frame). OR'd into keyboard pad mask.

[s_fmv_init / s_snd_ticks / s_snd_done promoted to file scope]
Rationale: Were block-scope statics inside the addr==0x8001EFE8 block. Need file-scope visibility
for savestate accessor functions. Identical runtime behavior — static lifetime unchanged.
